defaultA number of scientific studies have been conducted which are relevant to the 
defaultenvironmental impact of 
defaultcarrier bags:  
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;defaultIn February 2011 the Environment Agency released a study that concluded that:
default• The environmental impact of all types of carrier bag is dominated by resource use and production stages. Transport, secondary packaging and end-of-life management generally have a minimal influence on their performance.
default• Whatever type of bag is used, the key to reducing the impacts is to reuse it as
defaultmany times as possible and where reuse for shopping is not practicable, other
defaultreuse, e.g. to replace bin liners, is beneficial.
default• The reuse of conventional HDPE and other lightweight carrier bags for shopping and/or as bin-liners is pivotal to their environmental performance and reuse as bin liners produces greater benefits than recycling bags.
default• Starch-polyester blend bags have a higher global warming potential and 
defaultabiotic
defaultdepletion than conventional polymer bags, due both to the increased weight of
defaultmaterial in a bag and higher material production impacts.
default&#xa0;
defaultFurther the report states   “
defaultThe starch-polyester bag degrades fully to methane and carbon dioxide in landfill, producing a higher global warming impact from the end-of-life than the paper bag, which does not fully degrade in landfill”.
default&#xa0;
defaultAnd further 
default“The starch-polyester bag had the highest impact in seven of the nine impact categories considered. This was partially due to it weighing approximately twice that of the conventional HDPE bags but also due to the high impacts of raw material production, transport and the generation of methane from landfill.”
default&#xa0;
defaultBiodegradable means capable of being broken down by bacteria or other living organisms. ‘
defaultBioplastics
default’ are made from natural materials such as corn-starch. Whilst this sounds like a green option, as per the EA report, the result is methane gas which is 23 times more damaging to the environment than carbon dioxide. C
defaultompostable plastic is generally made from corn, a crop that is resource intensive, requiring large quantities land, water, and resources such as fertilizers for production. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultAn alternative to starch based bio-degradable bags are bags that include “
defaultoxo
default-degradable additives” which are generally made of heavy metals. Oxidative degradation is a series of chemical reactions in which the long chains of polyethylene molecules are broken down into shorter lengths by the action of oxygen, ultra-violet light and/or heat. 
defaultDefra commissioned Loughborough University to undertake a research project which assessed the environmental impact of 
defaultoxo
default-degradable plastics across the life cycle. The key finding of this report was that 
default“defaultThe overall conclusion of this review is that incorporation of additives into petroleum-based plastics that cause those plastics to undergo accelerated degradation does not improve their environmental impact and potentially gives rise to certain negative effects”.default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultFurther : 
default&#xa0;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe length of time to degradation of 
defaultoxo
default-degradable plastic cannot be predicted accurately because it depends so much on the environmental conditions. It is suggested that 
defaultoxo
default-degradable plastics left in the open environment in the UK degrade to small fragments within 2 to 5 years. 
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOxo
default-degradable plastics are not compostable, according to established international standards EN13432 and ASTM 6400. 
defaultOxo
default-degradable plastics should not be included in waste going for composting, because the plastic fragments remaining after the composting process might adversely affect the quality and saleability of the compost. 
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt is thought that labelling the 
defaultoxo
default-degradable plastics as biodegradable can lead to confusion on the part of consumers, who may assume that biodegradable plastics are 
defaultcompostable. This may lead to contamination of the composting waste-stream with 
defaultoxo
default-degradable plastics. 
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBiodegradation of 
defaultoxo
default-degradable plastics can only occur after they have fragmented and then proceeds very slowly, for example, at a rate many times slower than that of a compostable plastic.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultRecyclingdefault   
defaultOxo
default-degradable plastics are 
defaultnot suitable for recycling with main-stream plastics.default The 
defaultrecyclate
default will contain 
defaultoxo
default-degradable additives that will render the product more susceptible to degradation.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLitter  defaultSome 
defaultoxo
default-degradable producers maintain that their products are a solution to the littering problem because 
defaultoxo
default-degradable packaging will eventually degrade and then biodegrade. However, as the plastics will not degrade for approximately 2-5 years, they will still remain visible as litter before they start to degrade.
default&#xa0;
defaultAnother review 
defaultpublished recently in Environmental Science and Technology
default by a group of scientists including the polymer science division of the Indian Institute of Technology, finds that “degradable 
defaultpolyethylenes
default,“ used in one type of “recyclable” plastic bag, do not really disintegrate back into nature. The 
defaultpolyethylenes
default in the plastic bags studied are made by adding metals such as iron and cobalt to the mix of ethylene polymers, to speed
default up their oxidation. 
defaultBut while such hybrid plastic bags once discarded, do indeed break into fragments relatively quickly, those shreds persist for a long timdefaulte.default 
