defaultedefaultven in quantities as low as 2% defaultdegradable plastic films cause significant, detrimental impacts to the quality of defaultplastic defaultrecyclatesdefault. These impacts are not only detrimental in terms of mechanical properties of the recycled material, but also involve visual impacts on the newly produced film”.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultIn this report, MEPs are calling for a phase out and/or 
defaultbandefault of 
defaultoxo
default-degradable materials
